data.text: @RetroNewsNow It still is a painful reminder of how divisiveness & hatred for our fellow man (and woman) leads to tragic results. What lessons have we learned?!
@RetroNewsNow I hope crabs are eating his rotting corpse at the bottom of the ocean

🇺🇸On May 2, 2011, Osama bin Laden, leader of the al-Qaeda terrorist network & the individual responsible for the 9/11 terrorist attacks, was killed by U.S. Special Forces during a raid on his compound in Pakistan https://t.co/Gve1rEjok1
The attacks killed 2,996, injured over 6,000 & caused at least $10 billion in infrastructure & property damage

On the morning of September 11, 2001, four jetliners were hijacked & crashed in a series of coordinated attacks by the al-Qaeda terrorist network. Two airliners destroyed the World Trade Center in New York City. One airliner hit the Pentagon & a fourth crashed in Pennsylvania https://t.co/JN5lII8ZJG
